## üõ† Technologies & Tools Used

- Cisco Router & Switch
- DHCP (Dynamic Host Configuration Protocol)
- Static & Dynamic IP Addressing
- Wireless Networking (WPA2/WPA3)
- Cisco Packet Tracer
- Windows / Linux End Devices

---

## üåê IP Addressing Scheme

| Device       | IP Address                   | Description     |
| ------------ | ---------------------------- | --------------- |
| Router (LAN) | 192.168.1.1                  | Default Gateway |
| DHCP Pool    | 192.168.1.10 ‚Äì 192.168.1.100 | Dynamic Clients |
| Subnet Mask  | 255.255.255.0                | /24 Network     |
| DNS Server   | 8.8.8.8                      | Google DNS      |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Router Configuration (Core Commands)

```bash
enable
configure terminal

ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.1.1 192.168.1.9

ip dhcp pool HOME_NETWORK
 network 192.168.1.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.1.1
 dns-server 8.8.8.8

interface GigabitEthernet0/0
 ip address 192.168.1.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown

enable secret strongpassword123

line vty 0 4
 password cisco123
 login
```

Security Configuration

Changed default router login credentials

Enabled WPA2/WPA3 encryption on Wi-Fi

Disabled unnecessary remote access

Applied basic firewall protections on router

Testing & Verification
Test Command Purpose
Gateway Reachability ping 192.168.1.1 Verify router access
Internet Access ping 8.8.8.8 Verify internet
DHCP Assignment ipconfig / ifconfig Check auto IP
LAN Communication ping <PC-IP> Verify internal network

‚úÖ Successful ping replies confirm correct configuration.
